If you add an amperand after a command you will have the ID of the command displayed
And you will know when did the command stop.

If you add an ampersand in a script it will allow the command to run in background.

sendfile is a command which allow the transfert replacing read and write

the nc (netcat) command deal with the TCP and UDP protocol.
	It can open TCP connections, send UDP packets,
     listen on arbitrary TCP and UDP ports, do port scanning, and deal with both IPv4 and
     IPv6.

	 -v more verbose
	 -z Just scan listening daemons whitout send data

"gpasswd -d [USERNAME] [GROUP]" is the commande to delete a user from a group